dataIdInfo.idAbs: Boundaries representing the two hundred and eighty- seven Voting Precincts of Fayette County. Precincts are created based on the boundary lines of the State Senate, State Legislative, Urban County Council, Magisterial, and School Board Districts. Voting Precinct boundaries are established and maintained by the County Board of Elections, with the approval of the State Board of Elections, and are current as of March 2013.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: As part of the community data layers, the voting precincts boundary map layer is an integral part of the Fayette County Board of Elections. Community data layers are accessed by personnel in the Fayette County Board of Elections for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production. More advanced user applications may focus on thematic mapping, summarization of data by geography, or planning purposes (including defining boundaries, managing assets and facilities, integrating attribute databases with geographic features, spatial analysis, and presentation output).
